            . I am a watchman. On the 28th of March, between ten and eleven o'clock at night, I was in Kingsland-road; I saw the prisoner skulking about shops, and peeping in at doors; I told him to go on, which he refused; I took him in charge, and the officer found these scissors on him.</p>
               <p>
            
