                     <interp inst="t18280410-172-person1003" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer; between ten and eleven o'clock that night I was coming up Union-street, and heard the prisoner abusing the watchman; I told him to go along; he said he was a gentleman; I took him, and found these scissors on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I have been to the shop two or three years to be shaved; I can be upon oath that I bought the scissors two years ago, and paid for them; I was waiting for a person who was not in the way.</p>
